\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator finds that the programme in terms of all the Criteria required for public institutions\'2C the programme meets the minimum requirements for accreditation. However\'2C the evaluator recommended accreditation with conditions. The Directorate notes that the evaluator made comments on Criteria that is not relevant for public institution.\line \line The purpose of the programme is clearly stated though the evaluator is of the view that the student numbers should be reviewed in relation as to whether the market has sufficient demand for a programme of this nature. In terms of the knowledge content in the programme\'2C the evaluator is of the view that it is intellectually credible. However\'2C there is an area which is absent and is not covered in the the content regarding the legal aspects of mining. The Institution is required to address this matter. The programme is designed taking into account the different aspects of mining and makes provision for hands on laboratory experience. This will be catered for at the Florida campus of the Institution. Provision is made for the development of a portfolio of evidence which does not require WIL. A budget for the programme has been uploaded and the SAQA document along with the detailed module outlines. \line \line The student admission and selection policies are clear and the provision has been made for RPL. The major concern here are the student according to the evaluator are the students numbers and these should be reviewed in light of the comment on whether there is a demand for the programme in the sector. \line \line As this is a public institution\'2C criteria 3\'2C 4\'2C 7 and 8 do not need to be completed.  \line \line UNISA is an ODL institution using study material and web-based learning such as UNISA\'E2\'80\'99s MyUnisa platform for online learning\'2C discussion forums and blogs. The online facility can be utilised for video on demand \'28vod\'29 and podcasts. Some commitment to face-to-face contact underpinned by video conferencing facilities and an excellent library service is therefore appropriate. Learning experiences and environments are developed through a team approach. There are processes in place to support at risk or under-performing students. The lecturers provide detailed feedback in the form of marking memos to students and individual feedback to students who need constructive feedback. Reviews will be undertaken regularly and due consideration given to the findings. \line \line With regards to assessment\'2C the Institution has provided the required details on the Assessment Policy and all protocols related to these. For the portfolio\'2C UNISA will assign mentors and provide guidelines on how to mentor the students. As indicated earlier\'2C RPL is in place. \line \line Based on the above\'2C the Directorate recommends that the programme be accredited with a condition. \cell \pard 

